<br>
Gatsu took a sip from his glass and looked at the many tables and people who wandered this establishment. As he thought, he remembered his only vision of his own death. He for so long wished for that death to finally claim him and end the suffering and pain that followed him like a shadow. But now there was something new that held his life and made it precious. <br>
<br>
Gatsu looks up from his drink and in a powerful yet pain filled voice he asks<br>
<br>
&quot;Can a man change his destiny? Can a life that is destined for pain and suffering for everyone around him be changed?&quot;<br>
<br>
Some of the patrons looked at Gatsu quite puzzled others still ignored him as yet another large warrior who had drank too much. Gatsu wondered what their answers would be he could not find any answers in himself...<br>
<br>
